entries.name: skos:Collection
entries.description: A meaningful collection of concepts.

entries.name: skos:Concept
entries.description: An idea or notion; a unit of thought.

entries.name: skos:ConceptScheme
entries.description: A set of concepts, optionally including statements about semantic relationships between those concepts.

entries.name: skos:OrderedCollection
entries.description: An ordered collection of concepts, where both the grouping and the ordering are meaningful.

entries.name: skos:altLabel
entries.description: The range of skos:altLabel is the class of RDF plain literals.

entries.name: skos:broadMatch
entries.description: skos:broadMatch is used to state a hierarchical mapping link between two conceptual resources in different concept schemes.

entries.name: skos:broader
entries.description: Broader concepts are typically rendered as parents in a concept hierarchy (tree).

entries.name: skos:broaderTransitive
entries.description: skos:broaderTransitive is a transitive superproperty of skos:broader.

entries.name: skos:changeNote
entries.description: A note about a modification to a concept.

entries.name: skos:closeMatch
entries.description: skos:closeMatch is used to link two concepts that are sufficiently similar that they can be used interchangeably in some information retrieval applications. In order to avoid the possibility of "compound errors" when combining mappings across more than two concept schemes, skos:closeMatch is not declared to be a transitive property.

entries.name: skos:definition
entries.description: A statement or formal explanation of the meaning of a concept.

entries.name: skos:editorialNote
entries.description: A note for an editor, translator or maintainer of the vocabulary.

entries.name: skos:exactMatch
entries.description: skos:exactMatch is disjoint with each of the properties skos:broadMatch and skos:relatedMatch.

entries.name: skos:example
entries.description: An example of the use of a concept.

entries.name: skos:hasTopConcept
entries.description: Relates, by convention, a concept scheme to a concept which is topmost in the broader/narrower concept hierarchies for that scheme, providing an entry point to these hierarchies.

entries.name: skos:hiddenLabel
entries.description: The range of skos:hiddenLabel is the class of RDF plain literals.

entries.name: skos:historyNote
entries.description: A note about the past state/use/meaning of a concept.

entries.name: skos:inScheme
entries.description: Relates a resource (for example a concept) to a concept scheme in which it is included.

entries.name: skos:mappingRelation
entries.description: These concept mapping relations mirror semantic relations, and the data model defined below is similar (with the exception of skos:exactMatch) to the data model defined for semantic relations. A distinct vocabulary is provided for concept mapping relations, to provide a convenient way to differentiate links within a concept scheme from links between concept schemes. However, this pattern of usage is not a formal requirement of the SKOS data model, and relies on informal definitions of best practice.

entries.name: skos:member
entries.description: Relates a collection to one of its members.

entries.name: skos:memberList
entries.description:
For any resource, every item in the list given as the value of the
      skos:memberList property is also a value of the skos:member property.

entries.name: skos:narrowMatch
entries.description: skos:narrowMatch is used to state a hierarchical mapping link between two conceptual resources in different concept schemes.

entries.name: skos:narrower
entries.description: Narrower concepts are typically rendered as children in a concept hierarchy (tree).

entries.name: skos:narrowerTransitive
entries.description: skos:narrowerTransitive is a transitive superproperty of skos:narrower.

entries.name: skos:notation
entries.description: A notation, also known as classification code, is a string of characters such as "T58.5" or "303.4833" used to uniquely identify a concept within the scope of a given concept scheme.

entries.name: skos:note
entries.description: A general note, for any purpose.

entries.name: skos:prefLabel
entries.description: A resource has no more than one value of skos:prefLabel per language tag, and no more than one value of skos:prefLabel without language tag.

entries.name: skos:related
entries.description: skos:related is disjoint with skos:broaderTransitive

entries.name: skos:relatedMatch
entries.description: skos:relatedMatch is used to state an associative mapping link between two conceptual resources in different concept schemes.

entries.name: skos:scopeNote
entries.description: A note that helps to clarify the meaning and/or the use of a concept.

entries.name: skos:semanticRelation
entries.description: Links a concept to a concept related by meaning.

entries.name: skos:topConceptOf
entries.description: Relates a concept to the concept scheme that it is a top level concept of.
